<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[190,1442,978,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,336,978,1002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body length 2.0– 
<quantity box="[555,650,978,1002]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
; subparallel, flattened, light brown with head, pronotum, bases of elytra and abdomen dark brown and legs yellow (
<figureCitation box="[843,932,1010,1035]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); moderately glossy, with fine and dense punctation and pubescence; faint meshed microsculpture present on forebody; head as wide as pronotum, postocular area about as long as diameter of eye, posterior angles rounded; eyes moderately large; antennae long, almost reaching posterior margin of elytra, antennomeres I–III distinctly elongate, IV–X slightly elongate, XI only slightly longer than preceding antennomere; pronotum slightly transverse, shorter than head, widest in middle of its length, as wide as head and abdomen but narrower than elytra, slightly depressed medially; elytra elongate and flattened, at suture about one-fourth longer than pronotum; abdomen subparallel, slightly narrowed apically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[921,996,1239,1263]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Male:</emphasis>
tergite VIII broadly arcuate apically (
<figureCitation box="[199,287,1272,1296]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII longer than wide, evenly rounded apically, antecostal suture widely separated from basal margin (
<figureCitation box="[430,516,1305,1329]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus with large bulbus, tubus short triangular, arcuate and strongly produced ventrally in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[798,888,1337,1361]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[914,1023,1337,1361]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Female:</emphasis>
tergite VIII very broadly arcuate apically (
<figureCitation box="[304,389,1370,1394]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII about evently rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[956,1041,1370,1394]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); spermatheca S-shaped, capsule club-shaped with moderate-sized apical invagination, stem slightly swollen at base (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1314,1403,1427]" captionStart="Figures 25–31" captionStartId="15.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[211,1418,289,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[192,1440,266,1783]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 25–31. Hydrosmecta dulcis Casey.25) Habitus in dorsal view.26) Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. 27) Male tergite VIII. 28) Male sternite VIII. 29) Female tergite VIII. 30) Female sternite VIII. 31) Spermatheca. Scale line for habitus = 1 mm, remaining scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169557/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
